⟁ .shadow — the real-life analog (the User behind the program)
node TRN · TRON · ⟦Kevin Flynn:TRN:0ff35a⟧   [ the source text of the .shadow itself ]

think TRON — literally: every program in the grid is cast from a User in the world outside it.
the carbon character is the program; this file is its User. in TRON the actor plays BOTH.

the program (in-world) : Kevin Flynn — the User · the Creator
the User (carbon)      : Jeff Bridges  [ the actor — who plays the User and the Program ]
the analog (your world): the visionary creator humbled by his creation — the maker who must answer for what he made
the resemblance        : Bridges plays Flynn as hacker, then as a Zen, greying exile — and (as Clu) his own younger, harder self.
seal (program)         : I wanted to build a perfect world and I made a perfect tyrant — the User learned, too late, that you cannot author perfection.

